# GitHub Dark UI — Design Criteria

Every UI screen MUST look and feel like GitHub's dark mode. Primer is the SAME design system GitHub uses — leverage it fully.

## ThemeProvider Setup

- Use `colorMode="night"` for dark pages, `colorMode="auto"` to follow OS preference
- Available schemes: `dark` (default), `dark_dimmed`, `dark-high-contrast`
- Primer components automatically adapt — NEVER override their internal colors

```tsx
<ThemeProvider colorMode="night" nightScheme="dark">
  <BaseStyles>
    {children}
  </BaseStyles>
</ThemeProvider>
```

## Surface Layering (Background Tokens)

GitHub layers surfaces using three canvas tokens. Use them to create depth without brightness hacks.

| Token | Purpose | Dark value |
|---|---|---|
| `canvas.inset` | Page/viewport background (recessed) | `#010409` |
| `canvas.default` | Primary surface (cards, panels, main content) | `#0d1117` |
| `canvas.subtle` | Elevated surface (hover states, secondary panels) | `#161b22` |

### Layering patterns

- **Full-page forms (login, settings):** `canvas.inset` for page → `canvas.default` for card
- **Dashboards:** `canvas.default` for page → `canvas.subtle` for cards
- **Sidebars/rails:** `neutral.emphasisPlus` is ONLY for navigation chrome (rail, header bars), NEVER for page backgrounds

## Text Tokens

| Token | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `fg.default` | Primary text (headings, body) |
| `fg.muted` | Secondary text (descriptions, timestamps, placeholders) |
| `fg.onEmphasis` | Text on emphasis backgrounds (badges, filled buttons) |

### Pairing rules (WCAG AA)

- `canvas.default` bg → `fg.default` text ✓
- `canvas.subtle` bg → `fg.default` text ✓
- `accent.emphasis` bg → `fg.onEmphasis` text ✓
- NEVER pair `bgColor-muted` with `fgColor-muted`

## Border Tokens

| Token | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `border.default` | Card borders, input borders, dividers |
| `border.muted` | Subtle separators, secondary dividers |

## Buttons — Let Primer Handle Them

Primer `<Button>` handles all color states internally (rest, hover, active, disabled, focus). NEVER override button colors with CSS.

| Primer variant | GitHub usage |
|---|---|
| `variant="primary"` | Primary CTA (green in dark mode) |
| `variant="default"` | Secondary actions |
| `variant="danger"` | Destructive actions |
| `variant="invisible"` | Inline/subtle actions |

For custom-styled buttons (e.g., Google sign-in), use `canvas.default` bg with `border.default` border — this creates a white/light button that contrasts against dark surfaces.

## Icons

- Use `@primer/octicons-react` for all standard icons
- For third-party brand icons (Google, Apple), create SVG components in `components-web/atoms/Icons/` — NEVER in app modules or utils
- Import brand icons from `@primer-guidy/components-web`
- Always pair icons with `leadingVisual` or `trailingVisual` prop on Button

## What is FORBIDDEN

```scss
// FORBIDDEN — filter cascades to ALL children, breaks buttons and inputs
.page { filter: brightness(0.75); }

// FORBIDDEN — neutral-emphasis is for badges/tags, NOT page backgrounds
.page { background-color: var(--primer-neutral-emphasis-plus); }

// FORBIDDEN — overriding Primer Button colors
.myButton { background-color: green !important; }

// FORBIDDEN — creating color variations with brightness
.card { filter: brightness(1.33); }
```

## What is REQUIRED

```scss
// REQUIRED — proper canvas layering
.page {
  background-color: var(--primer-canvas-inset);
}

.card {
  background-color: var(--primer-canvas-default);
  border: 1px solid var(--primer-border-default);
}

// REQUIRED — proper text colors
.heading {
  color: var(--primer-fg-default);
}

.description {
  color: var(--primer-fg-muted);
}
```

## Primer Primitives CSS — MANDATORY

Every web app MUST import `@primer/primitives` theme CSS in `global.css` BEFORE Tailwind. This sets ALL 200+ CSS variables that Primer components use internally (inputs, buttons, selects, form controls, etc.).

```css
/* global.css */
@import '@primer/primitives/dist/css/functional/themes/dark.css';
@import '@primer/primitives/dist/css/functional/themes/light.css';
@import 'tailwindcss/theme';
@import 'tailwindcss/utilities';
```

Without this, Primer components fall back to defaults — inputs lose contrast, buttons lose colors, form controls become invisible.

## CSS Variable Bridge

In addition to primitives CSS, use `buildThemeVars()` from `@primer-guidy/components-web` to bridge theme colors to `--primer-*` CSS custom properties for SCSS access. This is set at the app root layout. NEVER duplicate `buildThemeVars` across apps — it lives in `components-web/src/utils/`.

## Flash / Banner Alerts

- Use Primer's `<Flash>` with `variant` (warning, danger, success)
- Flash components handle their own theming — no custom color overrides
- For sticky banners: wrap in a positioned container, do NOT apply filters

## Responsive Dark UI

- Dark mode should feel spacious — use generous padding (`p-6`, `p-8`)
- Cards should have visible but subtle borders (`border.default`)
- Use `rounded-xl` for main cards, `rounded-lg` for inner elements
- Maintain clear visual hierarchy through token layering, not color hacks
